    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-04-26T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-04-26T15:00:00-05:00" n="435"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d435">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4304: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-26T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 26, 1922—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>98. You are advised as follows in reply to your telegram no. 164 of April 24, 4
                    p.m.</p>
                <p>Arrangements are being made by the Navy Department, in accordance with your
                    suggestion, to land men for reinforcements to the Legation Guard.</p>
                <pb facs="0814" n="694" xml:id="pg_694"/>
                <p>Department’s no. 180 of July 16, 1920, 2 p.m.,<note n="27" xml:id="d435fn27">
                        <ref target="frus1920v01#pg_443">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1920, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 443</ref>.</note> will guide you on
                    question of effort of diplomatic corps to prevent military operations about
                    Peking.</p>
                <p>What significance is there in the resignation of Chen?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
